1
00:00:14,292 --> 00:00:15,750
(Wooju / Barcode Tinnasit)

2
00:00:18,375 --> 00:00:20,083
(Raon / Jeff Satur)

3
00:00:22,208 --> 00:00:23,833
(Woo-hyuk / DION)

4
00:00:26,042 --> 00:00:27,958
(Q / Q)

5
00:00:30,208 --> 00:00:32,042
(Hachi / Jason) (Air / Alpha)

6
00:00:36,917 --> 00:00:41,667
"Wooju Bakery"
(Episode 1)

7
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:44,958
"Here we go."

8
00:00:49,625 --> 00:00:54,250
(Wooju Bakery)

9
00:00:56,167 --> 00:00:56,833
Nice work.

10
00:00:56,958 --> 00:00:58,500
Hello, everyone.

11
00:00:58,958 --> 00:01:00,333
We're opening tomorrow.

12
00:01:00,458 --> 00:01:01,292
We hope you'll come visit.

13
00:01:01,417 --> 00:01:02,625
Wooju Bread.

14
00:01:03,542 --> 00:01:04,792
Wooju Bread.

15
00:01:04,917 --> 00:01:06,018
We're counting on your support.

16
00:01:06,042 --> 00:01:07,167
Wooju.

17
00:01:07,292 --> 00:01:08,542
Hyung.

18
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:21,000
Wooju, you're amazing.

19
00:01:21,125 --> 00:01:22,917
This bread looks beautiful!

20
00:01:23,667 --> 00:01:25,083
Here, try some.

21
00:01:25,208 --> 00:01:27,750
It's just a test batch.

22
00:01:32,875 --> 00:01:36,625
This... tastes a little...

23
00:01:38,542 --> 00:01:40,333
Did I add too much salt?

24
00:01:40,458 --> 00:01:41,458
Or is it the yeast?

25
00:01:41,500 --> 00:01:43,333
How can I open a bakery like this?

26
00:01:43,458 --> 00:01:46,375
Wooju, has your sense of
taste not come back yet?

27
00:01:48,625 --> 00:01:49,792
Don't worry.

28
00:01:49,917 --> 00:01:52,625
We still have Dad's recipes, right?

29
00:01:52,750 --> 00:01:54,667
Just follow the recipe book.

30
00:01:55,333 --> 00:01:57,125
Can I really do this?

31
00:01:57,250 --> 00:02:00,042
Of course you can. Let's
get ready for the opening.

32
00:02:03,000 --> 00:02:04,083
Are you hungry?

33
00:02:04,208 --> 00:02:05,333
Me?

34
00:02:06,083 --> 00:02:07,375
I'll just eat the bread.

35
00:02:11,792 --> 00:02:13,750
Didn't you just say it tastes weird?

36
00:02:14,875 --> 00:02:16,542
But you made it. I'm heading out.

37
00:02:16,667 --> 00:02:18,750
See you later, hyung.

38
00:02:37,708 --> 00:02:43,208
Is this where they sell the most delicious
and beautiful bread in the universe?

39
00:02:45,458 --> 00:02:46,167
Welcome.

40
00:02:46,292 --> 00:02:48,625
This is "Wooju Bakery."

41
00:02:48,750 --> 00:02:50,000
I'm sorry, but...

42
00:02:50,125 --> 00:02:51,333
All the bread in our shop...

43
00:02:51,458 --> 00:02:53,500
is already sold out for today.

44
00:02:55,417 --> 00:02:56,958
I came all this way just to try it.

45
00:02:57,083 --> 00:02:59,792
It's such a shame I can't have any.

46
00:03:01,333 --> 00:03:02,333
(Closed)

47
00:03:03,667 --> 00:03:04,667
(Open)

48
00:03:32,708 --> 00:03:35,417
Dad, where do stars come from?

49
00:03:35,743 --> 00:03:39,243
Stars come from a
faraway "universe" [wooju].

50
00:03:40,899 --> 00:03:43,500
Wooju, isn't that my name?

51
00:03:43,625 --> 00:03:45,000
That's right.

52
00:03:45,125 --> 00:03:49,250
And the universe is
full of delicious bread.

53
00:03:50,083 --> 00:03:52,375
Wow, it looks so delicious!

54
00:03:57,042 --> 00:03:58,208
Huh?

55
00:03:59,167 --> 00:04:01,542
Dad, where did you go?

56
00:04:01,667 --> 00:04:04,542
Wooju, it's okay. Don't worry.

57
00:04:06,000 --> 00:04:09,458
Dad will always be by your side.

58
00:04:10,000 --> 00:04:11,333
Dad?

59
00:04:13,292 --> 00:04:16,417
Dad!

60
00:04:18,458 --> 00:04:19,667
Don't be afraid.

61
00:04:19,792 --> 00:04:22,500
When stars are first
born, they always tremble.

62
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:24,667
My Wooju, let's meet again!

63
00:04:24,792 --> 00:04:26,208
Dad, where are you going?

64
00:04:27,583 --> 00:04:31,833
Dad, take me with you! I'm scared!

65
00:04:32,750 --> 00:04:34,250
Dad!

66
00:05:05,083 --> 00:05:06,542
My home!

67
00:05:16,042 --> 00:05:17,292
You guys!

68
00:05:18,083 --> 00:05:19,417
Look!

69
00:05:20,042 --> 00:05:20,875
Earthling!

70
00:05:21,000 --> 00:05:22,250
Don't be alarmed.

71
00:05:22,375 --> 00:05:24,917
This is just a regular landing accident.

72
00:05:25,042 --> 00:05:26,667
Who are you people?

73
00:05:29,917 --> 00:05:31,958
Can you understand me, Earthling?

74
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:39,083
Hachi! Is the translator broken?

75
00:05:39,208 --> 00:05:40,708
No, it is working well.

76
00:05:40,833 --> 00:05:42,875
Then why are you speaking
a different language?

77
00:05:43,000 --> 00:05:44,625
I like this language.

78
00:05:44,750 --> 00:05:46,250
I can speak Thai and English.

79
00:05:46,375 --> 00:05:47,875
Stop messing around.

80
00:05:48,000 --> 00:05:49,792
Who on earth are you?

81
00:05:53,625 --> 00:05:59,708
My name is Blablalis
Romoromorian Ardi Raon.

82
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:05,500
We're from the planet Kauncilion.

83
00:06:06,458 --> 00:06:08,167
I don't care who you are.

84
00:06:08,292 --> 00:06:11,708
You're the ones who wrecked
my bakery, aren't you?

85
00:06:12,667 --> 00:06:14,375
How are you going to pay for my bakery?

86
00:06:14,500 --> 00:06:18,250
Earthling, your body's
chemical levels are surging!

87
00:06:18,375 --> 00:06:20,375
You should lower your blood pressure.

88
00:06:20,500 --> 00:06:21,976
Hachi, how do you say
that in the local language?

89
00:06:22,001 --> 00:06:22,709
Take it easy!

90
00:06:22,833 --> 00:06:23,667
Hey!

91
00:06:23,792 --> 00:06:25,250
How can I be calm?

92
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:28,226
The grand opening is tomorrow, and
you crash into my shop and set it on fire!

93
00:06:28,250 --> 00:06:29,500
What do you want me to do?

94
00:06:29,625 --> 00:06:32,208
It was just a regular landing accident.

95
00:06:32,875 --> 00:06:33,625
Anyway, don't worry.

96
00:06:33,750 --> 00:06:36,167
It'll be covered by our
space travel insurance.

97
00:06:36,292 --> 00:06:37,542
Insurance money?

98
00:06:42,083 --> 00:06:43,208
When will I get it?

99
00:06:45,333 --> 00:06:47,417
For them to investigate this far...

100
00:06:47,542 --> 00:06:50,792
In Earth time, it would be about...

101
00:06:53,458 --> 00:06:54,583
A year?

102
00:06:55,292 --> 00:06:58,333
A year? Are you kidding me?

103
00:06:58,458 --> 00:07:00,208
I have a bakery to open tomorrow!

104
00:07:00,333 --> 00:07:01,583
Let's go to the police station.

105
00:07:01,708 --> 00:07:02,958
The police?

106
00:07:05,417 --> 00:07:07,875
The kind that lock us up and dissect us?

107
00:07:08,208 --> 00:07:10,167
Is that an Earthling custom?

108
00:07:11,000 --> 00:07:13,208
- Hey!
- Let's make a deal.

109
00:07:13,958 --> 00:07:14,708
What kind of deal?

110
00:07:14,833 --> 00:07:16,125
We have money in our spaceship.

111
00:07:16,250 --> 00:07:18,000
I'll go exchange it quickly.

112
00:07:18,125 --> 00:07:19,393
I'll give it to you before the
insurance money comes through.

113
00:07:19,417 --> 00:07:20,917
What kind of nonsense is this?

114
00:07:21,042 --> 00:07:22,458
That piece of junk is a spaceship?

115
00:07:22,583 --> 00:07:23,875
Yes, a spaceship.

116
00:07:24,000 --> 00:07:25,042
That's a car.

117
00:07:25,167 --> 00:07:28,042
Where the hell did you learn Thai?

118
00:07:28,500 --> 00:07:31,458
Hachi! This Earthling's
adrenaline is through the roof.

119
00:07:31,583 --> 00:07:33,383
He might get too excited
and start screaming.

120
00:07:33,458 --> 00:07:34,875
Stabilize his nerve cells, quickly.

121
00:07:35,000 --> 00:07:36,833
You maniacs!

122
00:07:42,667 --> 00:07:43,667
Prince.

123
00:07:43,708 --> 00:07:44,833
Hachi.

124
00:07:45,542 --> 00:07:46,958
Why did you shoot him?

125
00:07:47,083 --> 00:07:48,708
I didn't kill him.

126
00:07:54,000 --> 00:07:55,542
Let's get out of here first.

127
00:08:06,500 --> 00:08:09,708
So you're saying there were
strange men here just now?

128
00:08:09,833 --> 00:08:11,292
Are you sure you didn't see things?

129
00:08:11,417 --> 00:08:12,792
Dong-myeong is here.

130
00:08:13,583 --> 00:08:14,792
Dong-myeong...

131
00:08:15,125 --> 00:08:16,375
Wooju!

132
00:08:18,375 --> 00:08:19,375
Are you hurt?

133
00:08:21,042 --> 00:08:22,292
Are you okay?

134
00:08:22,417 --> 00:08:24,667
You're not even in night shift today, though.

135
00:08:25,375 --> 00:08:26,667
Yes, sir.

136
00:08:27,792 --> 00:08:30,208
But you know the owner of this bakery?

137
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:33,625
We've practically lived
together since we were kids.

138
00:08:33,750 --> 00:08:35,917
He's like a real brother to me.

139
00:08:37,083 --> 00:08:38,333
Wooju, are you all right?

140
00:08:38,458 --> 00:08:39,667
It's the rescue team, right?

141
00:08:41,792 --> 00:08:43,250
I think it's the rescue team?

142
00:08:45,417 --> 00:08:48,375
What kind of rescue team is this sloppy?

143
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:50,875
It looks like a crash landing.

144
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:53,917
Bro, what should I do?

145
00:08:54,042 --> 00:08:55,602
The shop was supposed to open tomorrow.

146
00:08:56,375 --> 00:08:57,500
It's all ruined.

147
00:08:57,625 --> 00:08:58,875
It's going to be okay.

148
00:08:59,292 --> 00:09:02,833
There's a lot of smoke, but
not much actually burned.

149
00:09:04,417 --> 00:09:06,083
Though the walls are a bit cracked.

150
00:09:06,750 --> 00:09:09,230
Let's clean this up first, and
we'll open tomorrow as planned.

151
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,792
Hyung, we have to find them.

152
00:09:13,750 --> 00:09:15,500
I've never seen those two Thai guys before.

153
00:09:15,625 --> 00:09:16,958
But I'm sure of it.

154
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:19,750
They're definitely the culprits.

155
00:09:21,833 --> 00:09:23,083
Thai guys?

156
00:09:25,000 --> 00:09:27,250
Got it. Wooju, wait here for a second.

157
00:09:30,708 --> 00:09:33,125
The rescue team's investigation
came to the same conclusion.

158
00:09:33,250 --> 00:09:36,083
It was just a lot of smoke, not a big fire.

159
00:09:36,208 --> 00:09:41,000
The owner here said a car crashed
into the shop and started a huge fire.

160
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:44,199
As you can see, there are
almost no signs of a fire.

161
00:09:44,200 --> 00:09:47,499
He was probably drunk
driving. That's got to be it.

162
00:09:47,500 --> 00:09:49,417
It looks like he just
crashed straight into it.

163
00:09:49,542 --> 00:09:53,333
He said that when the fire started,
there were two Thai-speaking men here.

164
00:09:53,458 --> 00:09:57,000
There are no signs of a break-in at all.

165
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,958
We have our conclusion.

166
00:10:07,958 --> 00:10:10,625
The car crashed, creating sparks.

167
00:10:10,750 --> 00:10:15,208
Then it hit the gas tank, "Bang!"

168
00:10:15,333 --> 00:10:18,458
That matches the explosion
the residents heard.

169
00:10:19,125 --> 00:10:21,500
But there are no signs of a gas explosion.

170
00:10:21,625 --> 00:10:24,000
Just write what I told you to write.

171
00:10:24,125 --> 00:10:27,542
No one's going to check anyway.

172
00:10:46,333 --> 00:10:48,083
You guys, don't run!

173
00:10:48,417 --> 00:10:50,125
Hey, stop!

174
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,792
Stop right there!

175
00:10:51,917 --> 00:10:53,125
Don't run.

176
00:10:53,500 --> 00:10:54,917
Hyung! Hyung!

177
00:10:55,375 --> 00:10:56,708
Wooju!

178
00:10:57,792 --> 00:10:59,333
I really saw them.

179
00:11:01,167 --> 00:11:05,542
I saw them clearly.

180
00:11:05,667 --> 00:11:08,000
I saw both of their faces.

181
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:09,792
What did they look like?

182
00:11:09,917 --> 00:11:14,167
One was wearing a sparkly stage outfit.

183
00:11:14,542 --> 00:11:17,875
The other was in a dog onesie.

184
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,417
They were both weird.

185
00:11:24,583 --> 00:11:27,250
Hyung, tonight...

186
00:11:27,875 --> 00:11:32,208
Can I sleep at your
place? I'm a little scared.

187
00:11:36,792 --> 00:11:39,417
I'm really scared. Please let me stay.

188
00:11:39,542 --> 00:11:41,942
It's not like we didn't have
sleepovers when we were kids...

189
00:12:13,625 --> 00:12:16,458
Who are you, and what are you doing here?

190
00:12:18,250 --> 00:12:20,042
Just as I thought.

191
00:12:20,167 --> 00:12:23,208
Humans have such bad memories.

192
00:12:23,542 --> 00:12:25,875
I'll say it again.

193
00:12:26,000 --> 00:12:32,958
My name is Blablalis
Romoromorian Ardi Raon.

194
00:12:33,083 --> 00:12:36,250
You can just call me Raon. This is Hachi.

195
00:12:44,042 --> 00:12:45,125
Are you guys real?

196
00:12:45,250 --> 00:12:46,458
I'm not seeing things, am I?

197
00:12:46,575 --> 00:12:49,260
From a quantum mechanics perspective,
particles also have the properties of waves.

198
00:12:49,292 --> 00:12:50,934
And waves have the properties of particles.

199
00:12:50,958 --> 00:12:53,792
So determining if something truly exists
is not that simple.

200
00:12:53,917 --> 00:12:55,750
"I think, therefore I am."

201
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:57,167
Then what are you?

202
00:12:57,292 --> 00:12:58,792
Walking around in a dog costume?

203
00:12:59,750 --> 00:13:01,500
What Hachi is wearing is special equipment.

204
00:13:01,625 --> 00:13:05,208
It's the uniform of the kingdom's
top astronaut and engineer.

205
00:13:05,917 --> 00:13:08,309
It can also transform into a humanoid form
during long voyages to save energy.

206
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:10,500
I have no idea what you're talking about.

207
00:13:10,625 --> 00:13:13,875
Who are you, and why are you here?

208
00:13:17,667 --> 00:13:19,917
From the perspective of Earthlings...

209
00:13:21,125 --> 00:13:22,792
we're aliens.

210
00:13:22,917 --> 00:13:25,167
What? Aliens?

211
00:13:35,458 --> 00:13:36,792
What do you think you're doing?

212
00:13:47,917 --> 00:13:48,667
You lunatics.

213
00:13:48,792 --> 00:13:50,992
You set fire to my place
and think you can just run off?

214
00:13:51,042 --> 00:13:51,708
What on earth is going on?

215
00:13:51,826 --> 00:13:52,701
Barging into my room...

216
00:13:52,833 --> 00:13:55,083
Are you trying to end up in jail?

217
00:13:55,917 --> 00:13:57,375
Jail food?

218
00:13:57,708 --> 00:14:01,750
You mean that stuff that
was just made downstairs?

219
00:14:01,875 --> 00:14:04,375
That stuff was disgusting.

220
00:14:04,958 --> 00:14:07,250
If we get locked up and have to eat that...

221
00:14:07,375 --> 00:14:08,417
it would be miserable.

222
00:14:08,535 --> 00:14:09,576
It was terrible.

223
00:14:09,708 --> 00:14:13,042
What... are you people talking about?

224
00:14:22,042 --> 00:14:23,625
Who's this guy?

225
00:14:27,624 --> 00:14:28,833
(Wooju Bakery)

226
00:14:29,583 --> 00:14:31,000
There's one over there.

227
00:14:32,750 --> 00:14:33,750
And another one there.

228
00:14:36,583 --> 00:14:37,958
This is unacceptable!

229
00:15:16,250 --> 00:15:18,042
Clean this mess up, you freak!

230
00:15:18,167 --> 00:15:19,833
Looks like you're the freak here.

231
00:15:29,583 --> 00:15:32,792
We... didn't order jjajangmyeon, though.

232
00:15:34,125 --> 00:15:34,792
Is that the rescue team?

233
00:15:34,917 --> 00:15:35,708
Who are you?

234
00:15:35,833 --> 00:15:40,125
I'm Jirol. I transport
the galaxy's food supply.

235
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:43,042
The galaxy's food supply?

236
00:15:48,167 --> 00:15:49,833
So it really was a crash landing.

237
00:15:49,958 --> 00:15:52,792
I thought it was the rescue team.
I got my hopes up for nothing.

238
00:15:52,917 --> 00:15:56,458
You'll have to bite the
bullet and stick it out here too.

239
00:15:57,000 --> 00:15:58,375
But we'll be going back soon.

240
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,393
That's what I thought,
that I'd be back home soon.

241
00:16:00,417 --> 00:16:02,167
But in Earth time...

242
00:16:02,292 --> 00:16:04,208
it's been a hundred years. A full century.

243
00:16:04,333 --> 00:16:07,333
We're from the House of Blablalis.

244
00:16:10,250 --> 00:16:13,208
What? A prince of Blablalis?

245
00:16:13,333 --> 00:16:16,917
The prince from the Kauncilion?

246
00:16:21,125 --> 00:16:25,792
Old man!

247
00:16:26,417 --> 00:16:28,583
See? I told you I was right.

248
00:16:30,208 --> 00:16:32,167
That guy! He's actual royalty.

249
00:16:32,292 --> 00:16:34,125
Blablalis?

250
00:16:34,175 --> 00:16:35,601
Doesn't that make him the Crown Prince?

251
00:16:35,625 --> 00:16:36,768
It looks like they really did crash-land.

252
00:16:36,792 --> 00:16:39,625
If he's the Crown Prince, a
rescue team is sure to come.

253
00:16:39,750 --> 00:16:41,583
Get closer. Stick with them.

254
00:16:41,708 --> 00:16:44,708
If we want to get out of here with
them, we need to get on their good side.

255
00:16:44,875 --> 00:16:47,375
The House of Blablaris...

256
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:51,208
is the supreme royal family that unites
hundreds of thousands of alien species.

257
00:16:51,333 --> 00:16:55,125
Without them, the galaxy
would be in total chaos.

258
00:16:55,250 --> 00:16:59,125
A rescue team will definitely come for
the Prince of Blablaris.

259
00:16:59,250 --> 00:16:59,958
And that means...

260
00:17:00,083 --> 00:17:04,250
after 116 years, 8 months,
and 37 days on Earth...

261
00:17:04,375 --> 00:17:06,000
I can finally go home.

262
00:17:06,125 --> 00:17:07,934
Are you wondering why
an alien looks so... normal?

263
00:17:07,958 --> 00:17:11,000
What, you thought we'd
look like this? Or maybe this?

264
00:17:11,125 --> 00:17:13,458
You Earthlings have
such a poor imagination.

265
00:17:13,583 --> 00:17:15,458
Is it all the oxygen you breathe?

266
00:17:15,583 --> 00:17:17,917
Aliens don't have a fixed appearance.

267
00:17:18,042 --> 00:17:21,500
We just take this form
to blend in with you.

268
00:17:21,625 --> 00:17:23,625
So while we wait to be rescued...

269
00:17:23,750 --> 00:17:25,583
some of us open auto repair shops,

270
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,125
some become fortune-tellers,

271
00:17:27,250 --> 00:17:29,167
and others get into pyramid schemes.

272
00:17:29,292 --> 00:17:32,212
Me? As you can see, I just play the
fool and hang around the neighborhood.

273
00:17:32,333 --> 00:17:33,518
What, you still don't believe me?

274
00:17:33,542 --> 00:17:35,375
You want proof?

275
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,500
Then put on some music with a beat.

276
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:40,792
Ah... I can't stop!

277
00:17:41,042 --> 00:17:43,208
If they dance, they must be an alien.

278
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:45,875
We can't help but move when we hear a beat.

279
00:17:47,208 --> 00:17:49,167
Okay, shh! Don't get too friendly.

280
00:17:49,292 --> 00:17:51,917
We've been living among you all along.

281
00:17:52,500 --> 00:17:54,875
Mwahahahaha!

282
00:17:55,792 --> 00:17:57,083
About what happened yesterday...

283
00:17:57,208 --> 00:18:00,583
The victim said they saw a stranger.

284
00:18:00,708 --> 00:18:01,917
Sir.

285
00:18:04,208 --> 00:18:07,625
This is a metal fragment we
found at the scene yesterday.

286
00:18:07,750 --> 00:18:10,417
It's not any metal found on Earth.

287
00:18:13,708 --> 00:18:16,250
Hello, is this the psychiatric hospital?

288
00:18:17,167 --> 00:18:19,268
I'd like to bring someone
in for an appointment at two.

289
00:18:19,292 --> 00:18:20,375
Okay.

290
00:18:21,083 --> 00:18:22,750
He said to come by at two.

291
00:18:23,667 --> 00:18:25,625
Take this with you.

292
00:18:26,910 --> 00:18:29,076
I don't need a shrink,
this needs to be sent to NASA.

293
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:32,042
Just get back to work.

294
00:18:33,625 --> 00:18:35,145
What are we going to do with this car?

295
00:18:36,375 --> 00:18:38,917
That's not a car. It's a spaceship.

296
00:18:39,417 --> 00:18:42,708
It just took a form that
would be familiar to Earthlings.

297
00:18:42,833 --> 00:18:45,500
Cut the crap. What are
we doing with this thing?

298
00:18:49,958 --> 00:18:51,875
Let's just leave it here for now.

299
00:18:52,000 --> 00:18:55,375
It'll be a nice tourist
attraction for the Earthlings.

300
00:19:02,667 --> 00:19:04,750
Why do we have to put everything back?

301
00:19:04,875 --> 00:19:06,625
Is that a rule on Earth?

302
00:19:09,375 --> 00:19:10,768
The grand opening is
delayed because of you.

303
00:19:10,792 --> 00:19:13,250
Didn't you say you'd pay me back in cash?

304
00:19:13,375 --> 00:19:15,000
Then give me the money now!

305
00:19:15,125 --> 00:19:17,000
Right now...

306
00:19:19,500 --> 00:19:21,250
I don't have any...

307
00:19:22,333 --> 00:19:22,833
money.

308
00:19:22,958 --> 00:19:25,278
"Currency Exchange - Earth
Branch 16 / House of Blablaris"

309
00:19:27,708 --> 00:19:29,083
What's that?

310
00:19:29,583 --> 00:19:31,708
Isn't that just a kid's marble?

311
00:19:32,792 --> 00:19:34,792
This is money where I come from.

312
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:37,792
And it's very valuable.

313
00:19:38,292 --> 00:19:40,125
It's just been shrunken down to this size.

314
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:42,917
It just looks like a marble to me.

315
00:19:45,083 --> 00:19:45,917
Hold on.

316
00:19:46,042 --> 00:19:49,833
(Incantation)

317
00:19:49,958 --> 00:19:51,167
What is that?

318
00:19:51,292 --> 00:19:52,667
See?

319
00:20:01,958 --> 00:20:05,375
(Incantation)

320
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:21,667
What is that?

321
00:20:22,708 --> 00:20:24,417
Is that an Earthling?

322
00:20:24,542 --> 00:20:27,458
Why did you bring an
Earthling to an exchange?

323
00:20:27,583 --> 00:20:28,833
That's against the rules.

324
00:20:28,958 --> 00:20:32,458
We just crash-landed yesterday.
We don't know the rules.

325
00:20:32,583 --> 00:20:33,792
Sorry.

326
00:20:34,375 --> 00:20:36,125
The signal is weak here on Earth.

327
00:20:36,250 --> 00:20:38,583
So foreign currency is almost worthless.

328
00:20:38,708 --> 00:20:40,268
Do you still want to make the exchange?

329
00:20:43,542 --> 00:20:44,667
Be honest with me.

330
00:20:44,792 --> 00:20:46,250
You're a con artist, aren't you?

331
00:20:46,375 --> 00:20:48,615
This isn't even enough to
cover the repairs for my shop.

332
00:20:49,125 --> 00:20:51,625
Let alone be enough for compensation.

333
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:53,583
Oh, really?

334
00:20:54,708 --> 00:20:55,750
So...

335
00:20:55,875 --> 00:20:57,583
what can you do with this much money?

336
00:20:57,708 --> 00:21:00,125
Maybe where you're from,

337
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:01,708
this is a month's salary.

338
00:21:01,833 --> 00:21:05,292
But here, you can earn this
by working hard for 15 hours.

339
00:21:05,417 --> 00:21:06,750
What?

340
00:21:06,875 --> 00:21:08,125
Fifteen hours?

341
00:21:17,667 --> 00:21:19,250
Hold your hands up.

342
00:21:20,208 --> 00:21:22,417
This is...
What are you doing?

343
00:21:22,542 --> 00:21:23,542
I'm putting you to work.

344
00:21:23,625 --> 00:21:25,458
So I don't have to pay you?

345
00:21:25,583 --> 00:21:26,458
What are you talking about?

346
00:21:26,583 --> 00:21:28,958
Of course you have to pay me back.

347
00:21:30,042 --> 00:21:31,625
Then I don't want to work.

348
00:21:32,583 --> 00:21:34,500
I'd rather just pay you the money.

349
00:21:36,417 --> 00:21:37,833
This is unbelievable.

350
00:21:37,958 --> 00:21:39,958
You're not even a
little bit sorry, are you?

351
00:21:40,083 --> 00:21:42,250
Don't you see all this burnt equipment?

352
00:21:42,375 --> 00:21:44,167
And the power outage?

353
00:21:44,292 --> 00:21:46,852
I'm trying to cut you some slack
since you're stranded on Earth.

354
00:21:46,917 --> 00:21:48,875
I'm not holding it against you.

355
00:21:51,167 --> 00:21:52,583
Sign your name here.

356
00:21:52,708 --> 00:21:53,500
What's this?

357
00:21:53,625 --> 00:21:54,708
It's a contract.

358
00:21:54,833 --> 00:21:57,958
You'll work for me for 10
years until you pay off your debt.

359
00:21:58,083 --> 00:22:00,125
That includes repair costs and interest.

360
00:22:07,458 --> 00:22:10,250
Oh shit! Prince, the police are here.

361
00:22:11,125 --> 00:22:13,167
You called the police?

362
00:22:15,250 --> 00:22:17,050
I'll work at your bakery
to pay off the debt.

363
00:22:22,833 --> 00:22:23,976
Please, don't call the police.

364
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:25,708
(Wooju Bakery)

365
00:22:32,000 --> 00:22:34,083
We just arrived on earth with the princess.

366
00:22:35,285 --> 00:22:40,243
We plan to rescue the prince by searching
the place where the prince is presumed to be.

367
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:51,792
The princess has a question.

368
00:22:52,708 --> 00:22:54,458
If we've found the prince,

369
00:22:55,208 --> 00:22:56,833
will the King keep his promise?
